<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Bank Piles Losses of 510 Million Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Indian Bank Chairman S. Rajagopal
said Thursday that the scam-hit bank has already run up losses of
20 billion rupees (510 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
He said the bank might find it impossible to wipe out these
losses for at least eight years without another round of bail-out
by the government in the form of write-off of recapitalized funds.
</P>
<P>
Claiming the higher non-performing assets level in 1997-98 was
due to the poor economic conditions and the tight money situation,
the bank chairman said the losses would have been less but for the
impact of a reduction in income and an increase in operating
expenses.
</P>
<P>
He announced plans to set up an asset reconstruction company to
take over its bad debts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
