<HEADLINE> World Cup Dope Tests All Negative </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 2 (Xinhua) -- All the dope tests carried out in the
56 first and second round matches had proved all negative, announced
FIFA official on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Keith Cooper, spokesman of FIFA at the World Cup finals, denied
rumours that one or more Argentine players had failed dope tests at
the World Cup.
</P>
<P>
"There are persistent rumours about this," Cooper said, "They
are completely untrue."
</P>
<P>
After each of the World Cup matches, two players from each team are
selected at random for a test. 
</P>
