<HEADLINE> Hagi Retires From Romania's National Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian footballer Gheorghe
Hagi announced Thursday here his official retirement from
Romania's national soccer team.
</P>
<P>
Hagi, 33, has been a soccer star for 16 years and played three
World Cup. He represented the national team in 115 international
games and scored 33 goals.
</P>
<P>
Hagi leaves the team, as he puts it, with the heart bleeding,
but proud to have played in Romania's team.
</P>
<P>
Hagi is optimistic about the future of Romania's soccer team
since there are a lot of talented young players in Romania.
</P>
