<HEADLINE> 27 Killed as Bus Falls Into Ditch in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-seven people, mostly
government servants and school children, were killed and several
others injured Thursday morning when an overloaded bus plunged
into a ravine in mountainous northern Pakistan, the Associated
Press of Pakistan reported.
</P>
<P>
The ill-starred bus was on its way to Mansehra, a major town in
northern Pakistan when the accident occurred. Some of the injured
were in a critical condition, APP said.
</P>
<P>
Initial reports reaching here had said at least 18 were killed
and 80 others injured. 
</P>
