<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romanian Captain Hagi Retires from International Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 2 (xinhua) -- Romanian captain Gheorghe Hagi
officially announced his retirement from the national team on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian team returned home one day after they were beaten
1-0 by Croatia in a round of 16 match at Bordeaux.
</P>
<P>
"The time has come to quit," Hagi said at a press conference
held at Bucharest, "Any story has a beginning and an end and the
end has come to my activity on the national team."
</P>
<P>
"I think I have accomplished my duty to my country's national
team. It's time to give up my place to younger players," said Hagi.
</P>
<P>
The 33-year-old Hagi has captained Romania in 54 matches over 15
years and accumulated a record 115 caps and scored 33 goals. He has
been hailed as Romania's most illustrious soccer player of all time.
</P>
<P>
"My last dream is to come back home to coach in Constanta," said
Hagi. He now plays for Galatasaray Istanbul, a leading Turkish
club. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
