<HEADLINE> French FM Discusses Kosovo Situation with U.S. Envoy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 2 (Xinhua) -- French Foreign Minister Hubert
Vedrine Thursday discussed the situation in the Yugoslav province
of Kosovo with visiting U.S. special envoy for former Yugoslavia
Richard Holbrooke.
</P>
<P>
French Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret said
after the meeting that both Vedrine and Holbrooke considered the
situation in Kosovo as "explosive."
</P>
<P>
The meeting was held at the request of Holbrooke, who wanted to
inform France about his latest contact with the rebellious "Kosovo
Liberation Army," or UCK, which is an Albanian armed rebel group.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that the two countries will maintain close contact
in the coming days over the situation in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Vedrine and Holbrooke also discussed the possible military
options by NATO in the Yugoslav province.
</P>
<P>
Latest reports from Kosovo said that ethnic Albanian rebels are
regrouping in the western part of Kosovo in expectation of a new
offensive by the Serb security force, who took a big coal mine
from the rebels earlier this week.  
</P>
