<HEADLINE> Security Council Decides to Maintain Sanctions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The President of the Security Council and Russian Ambassador
to the United Nations Lavrov Sergey told reporters that the
members of the Council did not reach an agreement on lifting
sanctions against Libya.
</P>
<P>
In 1992, the Security Council adopted resolution 748, which
requires all countries to deny permission to any aircraft to
take off from, land in or overfly their territory if it is
destined to land in, or has taken off from, Libya territory. The
air ban was designed to force Libya to surrender two suspects of
the Lockerbie bombing in 1988 which killed 270 people.  
</P>
