<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 2 (Xinhua) - Tanzanian vice president Omar
Ali Juma Thursday encouraged British businessmen to invest in
Tanzania whose economic environment has reportedly been
improving.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with the visiting Chairman of the British Overseas
Trade Board, Martim Laing, Dr Juma said that the government is
trying various ways to raise the country's competitive
capabilities in absorbing foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
