many investors to Tanzania," he said. "Others include abundant
natural resources, fertile land and adequate water supply."
</P>
<P>
Laing, who arrived here Tuesday to support British
participation in the Dar es Salaam International Trade Fair, said
that he was impressed by Tanzania's progress to revive the
economy, promising more British investment in the country.
</P>
<P>
A statement from the British High Commission has said that
Britain will play a very active role in the annual 22nd Dar es
Salaam International Fair which will officially open Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"Participants in the British Pavilion include British Airways,
the Commonwealth Development Corporation, CMC Land Rover, BP
(Tanzania) Ltd, Standard Chartered Bank and others," the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that in 1997, Britain exported 77
million pounds worth of goods to Tanzania, mainly road vehicles,
textile fibers and machinery.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania exports to Britain, primarily agricultural products,
were worth 33.1 million pounds over the same period.  
</P>
