<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Fifth European Economic Forum
started here on Thursday. The three-day meeting organized by the
European Local and Regional Powers Congress is to debate policies
of investments as well as regional development on pan-European
level.
</P>
<P>
"Political will is needed for the achievement of regional and
local development," the President of the Romanian Senate Petre
Roman told the opening session.
</P>
