<HEADLINE> Palestinian, Israeli Soldiers Square Off in Gaza </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Tension flared up in Gaza
Thursday as Palestinian and Israeli security forces squareed off
in a dispute over a road, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The standoff erupted when the Palestinian security forces
tried to prevent Israelis from entering the settlements inside
Gaza in retaliation for Israel's closing of a section of the
coastal road in Gaza, the Radio said.
</P>
<P>
Early Thursday morning, Israeli security forces closed the
coastal road between Khan Yunis and Deir Al-Balah and prevented
Abu Ali Shaheen, an official of the Palestinian National
Authority, from traveling to his office in Gaza via this road.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian security officials said that this was a violation
of the signed agreements which stipulate that Palestinians can use
this road without any hindrance.
</P>
<P>
Israel has sent reinforcements to Gaza in case the standoff
could escalate into conflict. Local reporters were prevented from
reaching the scene.
</P>
<P>
The situation in Gaza is very tense and many cars are still
parting on the side of the road in protest against its closure.
</P>
