<HEADLINE> UNICEF Offers Zambia 5.5M Doses of Oral Vaccines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Childrens' Fund
(UNICEF) has given Zambia 5.5 million doses of oral vaccines
worth of about 500,000 U.S. Dollars for the country's polio
vaccination program.
</P>
<P>
At the donation ceremony at Lusaka International Airport
Tuesday, UNICEF Representative Peter Mcdernott said that the
Zambian government has achieved tremendous success in its efforts
to eradicate polio, the Zambia News Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
