Organization Representative in Zambia, said that the preparations
for this year's polio vaccination program have reached an
advanced stage.
</P>
<P>
Boayue said that 90 percent of the Zambian children were
vaccinated last year and that 95 percent have been targeted for
this year's program.
</P>
<P>
And Gavin Silwamba, Director for the Central Board of Health,
said that the ministry of health will ensure that the vaccines
are distributed to all parts of the country. 
