<HEADLINE> Jordan, Iraq to Decide on Issue of Oil Supply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, July 2 (Xinhua) -- A Jordanian minister said here on
Thursday that during his ongoing visit here, the two sides will
determine the amount of oil Iraq will sell to Jordan in cheap
price in the second half of this year, the Iraqi News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Jordanian Minister of Energy and Mineral Resources Mohammed
Saleh Hourani said the oil Iraq has agreed to export to Jordan in
a protocol signed last year for the first half of this year has
reached the kingdom without any obstacles.
</P>
<P>
Under the deal signed last December, Iraq agreed to provide
Jordan with 4.8 million tonnes of oil and oil products this year
at reduced prices.
</P>
<P>
Hourani arrived here Thursday for a four-day visit.
</P>
<P>
He said that he will hold talks with Iraqi officials on the
establishment of oil pipelines from Iraq to Jordan, hoping that
the work will be finished as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
His delegation will "discuss Jordan's possibility of winning a
contract to develop one of Iraq's oil fields," the Jordanian
minister said.
</P>
<P>
He described the cooperation between the two countries as
excellent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
