<DOCNO> XIE19980703.0067 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Microsoft Pays for Using Internet Explorer Name </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Microsoft, the world's software
giant, has settled a trademark lawsuit, agreeing to pay 5 million
U.S. dollars for the right to continue using the name Internet
Explorer for its strategically important browser software.
</P>
<P>
On the second day of a jury trial in Chicago, Microsoft reached
a settlement with lawyers for SyNet, a defunct Illinois software
company that claimed the right to the Internet Explorer trademark.
</P>
<P>
The company first used the name for its Internet browser in
1994, about one year earlier than Microsoft did.
</P>
<P>
Microsoft argued that Internet Explorer is a common descriptive
term, meaning a device to explore, and could be used widely by
software makers in the industry.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that if a jury had decided SyNet in fact had the
right to the Internet Explorer name, Microsoft could have been
forced to spend an estimated 30 million U.S. dollars to remove the
words from its software, packaging and manuals.
</P>
<P>
SyNet founder Dhiren Rana, a British immigrant, claimed his
company was forced to ask for bankruptcy protection in part
because its legal battle with Microsoft cost too much.
</P>
<P>
Microsoft's Internet Explorer, which the company gives away for
free and distributes as part of its various Windows operating
systems, is at the core of the efforts by the government to show
that the software giant is extending its monopoly into the
Internet market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980703.0068 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Delhi Billed as World's Fourth Most Polluted City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- India's Minister of State for
Environment and Forests Babu Lal Marandi said Friday that the
World Health Organization has ranked New Delhi, capital of India,
as the fourth most polluted city in the world.
</P>
<P>
He told the Upper House of Parliament that New Delhi was the
fourth most polluted city in terms of suspended particulate
matter.
</P>
<P>
The city ranks the 27th in the world in terms of the amount of
sulphur dioxide in atmosphere, he said.
</P>
<P>
An action plan has already been prepared and an environment
pollution prevention and control authority has been set up for
protecting the environment and preventing pollution, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Central Pollution Control Board is also monitoring air
quality through 10 monitoring stations under the national ambient
air quality monitoring program, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
