<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belgian Unemployment Down in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The annual unemployment rate in
Belgium dropped to 11.7 percent in June compared with a year
earlier, or 31,000 persons fewer.
</P>
<P>
The Flemish-speaking northern part of the country witnessed
more improvement in employment as the jobless figure decreased by
23,000 persons, while improvement in the French-speaking southern
part of the country was not as much, only 5,000 persons less than
the corresponding period last year.
</P>
<P>
In the bilingual Brussels region, there were 2,500 persons less
on the jobless list in June.
</P>
<P>
Unemployment has been a pressing problem with European Union
member countries. Spain, France and Germany have also been
suffering from double-digit unemployment for the past several
months.
</P>
<P>
Luxembourg emphasized the issue of employment during its six
month presidency of the 15-nation union in the latter half of last
year.
</P>
<P>
Austria, which took over the EU presidency on July 1 from
Britain, also promised to stress the necessity of improving
employment during its tenure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
