<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> E.U. to Aid El Nino Victims of The Philippines, Uruguay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The European Union on Friday
pledged an equivalent of 1.43 million U.S. dollars in aid to the
victims in the Philippines and Uruguay who have suffered from El
Nino-caused freak weather.
</P>
<P>
Announcing the deal, the European Commission, executive arm of
the 15-member bloc, said the emergency aid will be managed by the
E.U. European Community Humanitarian Office, and the programs will
start in the coming few months.
</P>
<P>
The E.U. aid will finance food aid, health care and shelter for
families affected.
</P>
<P>
In the Philippines, El Nino caused a drought that left the
country with less than half its normal rainfall for the rainy
season and more than 700,000 people are facing serious food
shortages.
</P>
<P>
Commission officials said some people in the Asian country had
to eat poisonous plant roots that had already claimed some 50
lives.
</P>
<P>
In Uruguay, however, the problem is flooding triggered by
torrential rain. At least 8,000 people have been forced to
evacuate from their city dwellings so far. 
</P>
</TEXT>
