<DOCNO> XIE19980703.0083 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HKSAR government's Accounts for 1997-98 Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The total revenue of the
government of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR)
for the financial year 1997-98 amounted to 275.2 billion HK
dollars (35.28 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Its total expenditure was 194.3 billion HK dollars (24.91
billion U.S. dollars), thus resulting in a surplus of 80.9 billion
HK dollars (10.37 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The surplus is 3.9 billion HK dollar (500 million U.S. dollar)
higher than the revised estimate of 77 billion HK dollars (9.87
Billion U.S. dollars) announced by the Financial Secretary in his
Budget speech in February.
</P>
<P>
The government's accounts for the financial year 1997-98 which
ended on March 31 were published in the Gazette Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to the accounts, revenue was 600 million HK dollar
(76.92 million U.S. dollar) higher and expenditure 3.3 billion HK
dollar (423 million U.S. dollar) lower than anticipated at the
time of the revised estimate.
</P>
<P>
A government spokesman said: "despite the economic downturn,
overall revenue collections were in line with expectations."
</P>
<P>
"The underspending of less than two percent was spread across a
wide range of items," he said.
</P>
<P>
After taking account of the net worth of the Land Fund of 203.1
billion HK dollars (26.04 billion U.S. dollars), the government's
total fiscal reserves amounted to 457.5 billion HK dollars (58.65
billion U.S. dollars) at March 31, this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
