<HEADLINE> Conference Opens on Party Building in Universities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Seventh National Work
Conference on Party Building in Universities opened at the
Great Hall of the People in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Present at the opening were Hu Jintao, Wei Jianxing and Li
Lanqing, all members of the Standing Committee of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee Political Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Li hailed the remarkable achievements made in the field of
Party building in recent years due to efforts by Party
organizations in localities, universities and colleges.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the proportion of CPC-affiliated students has kept
rising in recent years, he said.
</P>
<P>
To arm the university teachers and students with Deng
Xiaoping Theory is the principal task for strengthening the
Party building work in universities and fundamentally ensuring the
normal operation of the universities to foster century-striding
builders and successors of the socialist modernization cause, Li
said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the CPC Central Committee has attached great
importance to helping university students study Deng Xiaoping
Theory.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping Theory must be included in college textbooks,
studied in classes, and kept in the brains of students, Li
stressed.
</P>
<P>
He said more qualified young university teachers should be
fostered who would be good both in moral and professional
skills. It is an imperative and urgent task, he added.
</P>
<P>
The conference is being jointly held by the Organizational
Department and the Publicity Department under the CPC Central
Committee. 
</P>
