<HEADLINE> EU Medical Aid for Russia, Ukraine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission approved
Friday further aid worth 1.565 million ECU (1.62 million U.S.
dollars) to Russia and Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
The lion's share of the medical aid package, 850,000 ECU in
all, will be used to help curb a tuberculosis surge in Siberia and
the Transcarpathians, the latter a mountainous region in Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
Another 465,000 ECU will be used in the prevention and
treatment of thyroid cancer in the aftermath of the Chernobyl
nuclear plant disaster.
</P>
<P>
The incidence of thyroid cancer among children affected by the
Chernobyl meltdown is still going up, according to health
organization sources.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission provided 250,000 ECU for relief
programs in northeastern Siberia, where fast-melting ice in freak
weather conditions has led to flooding that affected about 170,000
people.
</P>
<P>
Commission officials said many factory and public buildings had
been damaged, but further flooding is still expected. 
</P>
