<HEADLINE> German Unemployment Down 120,000 in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Germany's unemployment dropped by
120,000, to 4.075 million in June, German Chancellery Minister
Friedrich Bohl said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment rate, measured on the basis of
seasonally-unadjusted data, fell to 10.5 percent from 10.9 percent
registered in May, Bohl added.
</P>
<P>
If confirmed by final data to be released by the German Federal
Labor Office next Tuesday, it would represent the fourth
consecutive drop in Germany's unemployment since March.
</P>
<P>
The decline in unemployment bears special significance for
German Chancellor Helmut Kohl, who is geared up to campaign for a
record fifth term in the September 27 national elections. 
</P>
