<HEADLINE> Bierhoff Wary of Croatian Vengeance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- German striker Olivier Bierhoff has
warned that Germany should be wary of a stronger Croatia team
attempting to seek revenge in Saturday's World Cup quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
"This match is vengeance for the 1996 European championship for
Croatia. We'll have to be psychologicaly strong," said Bierhoff in
Nice on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Croatia lost to Germany 2-1 in Manchester during that championship
after defender Igor Stimac was sent off.
</P>
<P>
"I know that the Croatia team has a similiar style of play to
Yugoslavia, who we've already played, but they are tougher and more
focused," he added.
</P>
<P>
Bierhoff, who has signed AC Milan from Italian side Udinese, said
he would prove that he scored not simply because of good luck.
</P>
<P>
"Up until now, they used to say my success was just due to good
luck, but over the past two years, I've proven otherwise," he said.
</P>
<P>
But Bierhoff, who scored three goals in the tournament so far, said
his status in the team has changed in the past two years.
</P>
<P>
"In the European championships, despite the goals I scored, I
wasn't really counted upon. In the World Cup here, it's very nice to
have the confidence of the whole team." 
</P>
