<HEADLINE> Progress Slow in Repairing Breached Dike in Guangdong Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Little progress has been made by
soldiers who have been working hard since Tuesday to repair a
breached dike on a tributary of the Beijiang River in south
China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
So far, 11 vessels have been sunk by explosions to block the
opening, while three more boats are expected to be sunk at the
site.
</P>
<P>
Troops have been building a coffer dam near the breach. Work
has been delayed by the constant torrential floods, local
officials said.
</P>
<P>
Floodwaters have reached Sanshui City, submerging the entire
town of Baini, most of Jinben and part of Xinan. Local residents
have been removed to dry ground.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Minister of Water Resources Zhang Chunyuan is now on site
to guide the repair work. 
</P>
