<DOCNO> XIE19980703.0102 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fujian's Half-Year Economic Growth Rate Hits 11.3 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The economy of east China's Fujian
Province continued to grow steadily in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Fujian's gross domestic product totaled 136.5 billion yuan in
the first six months, up 11.3 percent from the same period last
year, according to official statistics released today.
</P>
<P>
A breakdown shows that Fujian's agricultural output value rose
8 percent year-on-year to 29.4 billion yuan in the January-June
period, while its industrial output value surged 16 percent to
112.4 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Fujian has set this year's economic growth rate at 11 percent,
3 percent higher than the national target.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics also show that Fujian's investment in fixed
assets rocketed 41 percent on a yearly basis to 16.47 billion yuan
for the January-June period. The growth rate is the second highest
nationwide and 28.3 percent higher than the national average.
</P>
<P>
Fujian also invested 4.48 billion yuan in technical renovations
in the first six months, a surge of 72.4 percent from a year
ago. The growth rate is the highest among all provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
In the January-June period, Fujian's exports totaled 4.45
billion U.S. dollars, up 3.4 percent from the same period last
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
