<HEADLINE> Tacconi: Italy, France to Go to Penalty Shootout </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Stefano Tacconi, Italy's former national
goalkeeper, predicted the World Cup quarterfinal between Italy and
France would be decided by penalty shootouts.
</P>
<P>
"I think that the match will be very intense, very physical,"
Tacconi told the Italian television RAI on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"The return of Zinedine Zidane will give an extra boost to the
French midfield, which is superior to Italy's," he added.
</P>
<P>
Tacconi said Italy had an upper hand in attacking with the likes of
Roberto Baggio, Alessandro Del Piero and Christian Vieri.
</P>
<P>
He said, "Italy have a very strong attack and should be looking to
score a goal against what is probably the best denfence in this World
Cup."
</P>
<P>
"I predict that the match will go to a penalty shootout, but I hope
that this will be a good day for Del Piero."
</P>
<P>
He said the vital quality for a goalkeeper was stay calm even in
the most dangerous situation.
</P>
<P>
"I think that the most important quality for a goallie is staying
calm. As regards to Italy's Gianluca Pagliuca and France's Fabien
Barthez, I think the Italian has the edge in this respect." 
</P>
</TEXT>
