<HEADLINE> British Leader Attends Seminars on Water, Aerospace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- "There exists a unique opportunity
for cooperation between the United Kingdom and China," said
British Deputy Prime Minister John Prescott here today.
</P>
<P>
Heading a trade mission of the British water industry and 10
leading UK aerospace companies, the visiting British leader today
addressed both the UK-China Water Sector Cooperation Seminar and
the Sino-UK Aerospace Industry Partnership Seminar.
</P>
<P>
In both addresses, he expressed his hope that "the visit will
further enhance the links between the two nations in politics,
economy and other areas."
</P>
<P>
Two important areas in bilateral cooperation are the use of
water resources and the aerospace industry, he said.
</P>
<P>
At today's seminar on water sector cooperation, British
visitors spoke on how to use and manage water resources followed
by a discussion with their Chinese counterparts.
</P>
<P>
Zhao Baojiang, China's vice-minister of construction, stressed
at the seminar that China will make positive use of foreign
capital and equipment for the development of wastewater disposal
and water resources administration.
</P>
<P>
With a total of 5.3 billion U.S. dollars by the end of
1997, Britain was the leading investor among European countries in
China.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Yuli, president of the Aviation Industry of China, said at
the aerospace seminar that regular exchanges between the aerospace
industries, enterprises and research institutions of China and
Britain have promoted cooperation between the two countries in
this sector.
</P>
<P>
Prescott said he will also take the trade mission to Xi'an and
Shanghai, and hold seminars in both places. 
</P>
</TEXT>
