<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stock Exchange Closes Down for Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The stock trading at the Shanghai
Stock Exchange (SSE), one of China's two bourses, continued
declining this week with the SSE Composite Index closing at 1335.13
points, down 3.64 percent from last week.
</P>
<P>
While the SSE 30 Index plunged by 4.14 percent compared with
last week to close at 3336.55 points on Friday, the last trading
day of the week.
</P>
<P>
The week's trading volume dropped by 10 billion yuan to stand
at 22.17 billion yuan. Of the 458 shares listed on the bourse,
only 75 gained this week.
</P>
<P>
The B-share trading continued to fall this week, with the
B-share index closing at 40.83 points, 1.57 percent less than last
week. The week's B-share trading volume was 65 million yuan, 20
million yuan lower than last week.
</P>
<P>
The trading in funds totaled 1.25 billion yuan, 455 million
yuan less than last week, while the trading in bonds also
decreased to 46.09 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
