<HEADLINE> Taiwan Compatriots Summer Camp Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The 15th Taiwan Compatriots Summer
Camp opened here today on the campus of Beijing University.
</P>
<P>
Sixty Chinese youngsters from Taiwan, the United States, Canada
and Brazil are attending the annual event. During the 16-day camp,
they are scheduled to visit a number of local historical sites
such as the Summer Palace, the Palace Museum and the Great Wall.
</P>
<P>
After activities in Beijing, the young people will tour a dozen
Chinese cities as well as some natural and historical spots
such as the Shaolin Temple and Longmen Grottos in Henan Province,
and the terra-cotta warriors and horses in Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony, Yang Guoqing, vice-president
of the All-China Federation of Taiwan Compatriots, said that the
summer camp is a good way to help young people from Taiwan and
overseas know about their motherland, foster their sense of
patriotism and increase their friendship with university students
in Beijing and other places. 
</P>
