<HEADLINE> Macao SAR Preparatory Committee Holds Second Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Macao Special Administrative
Region (SAR) Preparatory Committee held the second meeting
of its Working Group of Social and Cultural Affairs in Zhuhai, a
city in south China's Guangdong Province, today.
</P>
<P>
To date, the Macao SAR Preparatory Committee's four working
groups for administrative affairs, legal affairs, economic
affairs, and social and cultural affairs have all finished their
second meetings within a five-day period.
</P>
<P>
During today's meeting, members of the Working Group of Social
and Cultural Affairs expressed excitement over the speech made in
Hong Kong by Chinese President Jiang Zemin on July 1. Committee
members said the speech reflects the central government's concerns
about the public security in Macao and strengthens the
confidence of Macao residents in a smooth transfer to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
The working group deliberated the public order of Macao, and
mapped out a proposal to be delivered to the second plenary
session of the Macao SAR Preparatory Committee for further
consideration.
</P>
<P>
The working group also passed a work report, which is also
scheduled to be delivered to the second plenary session, and
discussed arrangements about Macao residents' holidays in the
December 20-31 1999 period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
