<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Drug Firm Donates Medicine to Elderly of Changsha </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Lingnan Pharmaceutical Factory
of Hong Kong has donated 200,000 yuan worth of medicine to the
elderly of Changsha, capital of central China's Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
The donation, the first such donation made to the mainland by
the factory, is intended to convey the affection of Hong Kong
people for their mainland compatriots, sources from the factory
said.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the company is concerned about the health
of the elderly and children of Hong Kong, and has been making
donations for many years. The company plans to make more
contributions to the health of the mainland residents in the
future, they said.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1923 in Singapore by a well-known practitioner
of Chinese medicine, Lu Manchang, the factory was moved to Hong
Kong in the 1950s. 
</P>
