<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Joint-Stock Firms Boom in Rural Hebei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Joint-stock firms are playing
an increasingly important role in the rural economy in north
China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
Hebei has more than 70,000 rural joint-stock cooperative firms
which account for approximately a quarter of the province's rural
output value, according to the provincial government.
</P>
<P>
Joint-stock cooperative enterprises make up over 80 percent of
all rural and township firms in the cities of Tangshan and
Shijiazhuang. In addition, more than 90 percent of rural
cooperative foundations have introduced joint-stock operations.
</P>
<P>
The joint-stock system covers wide-ranging areas, including
agriculture, forestry, aquatics and processing sectors. Hebei also
has some 4,000 joint-stock enterprises which specialize in
in-depth processing of farm produce.  
</P>
</TEXT>
