<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Friday as deals said investors
made selective pickings following through selling after
substantial gains in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
However, it still held on and rebounded in the wake of Japan's
plan to revive its economy, which saw yen and Tokyo Nikkei further
strengthen Friday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index eased 4.42
points to 473.78, the all-share Emas Index shed 0.85 of a point to
118.44, the Industrial Index was 0.40 of a point lower to 945.36
while the Second Board Index shed 0.20 of a point to 98.06.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 312 to 156 while 186 were unchanged and
270 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover shrunk to 83.568 million shares worth
149.445 million ringgit (about 36.1852 million U.S. dollars) from
Thursday's 159.146 million shares valued at 318.718 million
ringgit (about 38.5341 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover fell to 79.299 million shares worth
143.474 million ringgit (about 34.7394 million dollars) from
Thursday's 153.915 million shares valued at 311.086 million
ringgit (about 37.2675 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover eased to 4.269 million shares worth
5.970 million ringgit (about 1.4455 million dollars) from 5.231
million shares valued at 7.632 million ringgit (about 1.8479
million dollars) Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Off market deals declined to 7.937 million shares worth 7.821
million ringgit (about 1.8937 million dollars) from Thursday's
16.007 million shares valued at 21.603 million ringgit (about
5.2307 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange will be closed on July 6, in
conjunction with the Prophet Mohamed's birthday. 
</P>
