<HEADLINE> Russian Lawmaker Killed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Lev Rokhlin, a deputy of the Russian
State Duma (lower house of the parliament) was killed by his wife
Thursday night at his dacha outside Moscow, Itar-Tass news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
An official at the Federal Security Service said "there are no
signs of terrorism connected with an assassination attempt on a
political figure or political reasons for the killing."
</P>
<P>
Rokhlin, 51, former Chairman of the Duma Committee on Defense,
was shotted by his wife with his own weapon.
</P>
<P>
It was said that Rokhlin, who lived together with his wife at
his dacha, drank heavily of late. Therefore, it is not ruled out
that he could fall victim to domestic violence. Meanwhile, there
is also speculation that the killing could be connected with
commercial activities, the report said. 
