<HEADLINE> French Coach Says He Fears Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- French team manager Aime Jacquet said
he feared the Italian team, their quarter-final opponents at the
World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
"I fear Italy's realism, their thorough professionalism and
their ability to constantly adapt," said Jacquet, "I fear the
individual skills of each player and their great attacking
potential and also their characteristic ability to smother the
opposition."
</P>
<P>
But what Jacquet fears most about the Italian team is their
ability to counter-attack:"They move as one daunting block and
strike out with killer dagger thrusts. It is fatal to think that
Italy will sit back and defend." Jacquet said.
</P>
<P>
But Jacquet thinks his team still have the chance of beating the
Italian team:"Patience, optimism, and the excellence of those key
players that both teams possess will be decisive," said Jacquet,
"The team that can put these exceptional players in a position to
express themselves will win."
</P>
<P>
France will play Italy in a quarter-final match at Saint-Denis
on Friday. 
</P>
