<HEADLINE> Mozambican Govt Urged to Probe Death of Former </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Graca Machel, wife of Mozambique's
first president, the late Samora Machel, has urged the government
to take up action to find out the truth of the plane crash which
killed his husband, instead of staying indifferent.
</P>
<P>
Graca complained here to the press Thursday that the
Mozambican government had not done anything to clarify the death
of her husband 12 years ago in Mbuzine, South Africa, the
Noticias newspaper reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Last week, Graca told the Truth and Reconciliation Commission
(TRC) of South Africa about her views in this regard, noting that
South Africans and Malawians were also involved.
</P>
<P>
The TRC is responsible for the investigation of the cause of
Samora Machel's death on October 19, 1989.
</P>
<P>
She added that two Mozambican generals were also suspects in
the killing of her husband.
</P>
<P>
Investigations showed that the plane crash was caused by a
fake radio signal which divert the plane from its due course.
</P>
<P>
The plane crash also killed 34 people, including some
ministers, journalists, the president's security personnel and
the crew. 
</P>
