<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roberto Baggio Says Even Italy Not Favorite </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Italian striker Roberto Baggio said there
would be no favorites, including his own team, when competition goes
to quarterfinals in the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
"When you reach this stage in the competition there are no longer
any favorites. Everybody has a chance," said Baggio after the team's
training session in Senlis on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
As for Italy's quarterfinal opponent, Baggio said: "France is a
very strong team based on a solid defence, along with ball-winners in
midfield."
</P>
<P>
He added: "Didier Deschamps is one of them, I knew him at Juventus
where I appreciated not only the player but the person."
</P>
<P>
His teammate Alessandro Del Piero said Friday's quarterfinal at the
newly-built stade de France would be much like a final.
</P>
<P>
"This match will be like a final. The pressure will be the same for
both teams, but France will feel it even more because they are playing
at home," said Del Piero. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980703.0190 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Coach Aware of Team's Ability </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Italian coach Cesare Maldini is fully
aware of his team's ability and depth when they will take on hosts
France in the quarter-finals at Saint-Denis on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"I haven't yet made a final decision on the composition of the
team. I don't know how France will play, how they will line up, and
whether they will have fully recovered from their match against
Paraguay." said Maldini.
</P>
<P>
Maldini said:"As regards my players, I am confident:they are in
good condition physically and they want to put on a good performance."
</P>
<P>
Maldini said the host team not scared him:"It's true we are the
away team but we're used to this type of match. This quarter-final
match reminds me a little of the World Cup qualifier against England
at Wembley which we won 1-0."
</P>
<P>
Maldini said:"Our main strength is our self-belief. The further
we go, the more we become aware of what we are capable of. No
Italian team has ever been eliminated in the quarter-final of a
World Cup, but that's no guarantee." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
