<HEADLINE> Northeastern Liaoning Province Preparing for Flood Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Liaoning
Province is taking preventative steps to deal with possible
flooding of major rivers and reservoirs during the flood season
this year.
</P>
<P>
The province has put a billion yuan (120 million US dollars)
into repairs of flood damaged projects, dredging and clearing
flood-relief channels, and reinforcing dikes and dams.
</P>
<P>
According to the provincial meteorology departments, heavy
rains have hit most of Liaoning since April, and precipitation
is up 60 percent from the same period in normal years.
</P>
<P>
Provincial Governor Zhang Guoguang recently called on both
officials and people in various localities to increase their
awareness of possible flooding and adopt effective measures so as
to guarantee the safety of major rivers, reservoirs and
big and medium-sized cities.
</P>
<P>
Zhong Gang, director of the Provincial Water Conservation
Bureau, said local officials will be given training on how to deal
with possible floods and various supplies are being prepared for
fighting floods.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning was hit every year by floodings from 1994 on, and was
hit by a typhoon last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
