<HEADLINE> Japan Provides More Aid to Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Japanese government will provide
a grant aid of 800 million Yen (about 5.7 million U.S. dollars) to
Myanmar to help it increase food production in the border areas,
said a Press Release of the Japanese Embassy in Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
Notes were signed and exchanged here Thursday by Myanmar
Minister at the Office of the Chairman of the State Peace and
Development Council Brigadier General Abel and Japanese ambassador
to Myanmar Kazuo Asakai, said the Press Release available here.
</P>
<P>
This Grant Aid is to provide fertilizer and agricultural
machinery to the farmers in the poppy-growing areas along the
border to encourage "crop substitution" so as to eliminate
illicit cultivation of poppy, the Press Release added.
</P>
<P>
According to another Press Release, the Japanese government
Thursday also extended a grant aid of 9,232 U.S. dollars under the
grass roots grant assistance scheme for the HIV/AIDS prevention
program in the Shan State of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
