<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Urbanites Have New Fun In The Countryside </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- More of China's urbanites are
choosing to use their two-day weekends having fun in the
countryside, thanks to the growing number of village tours
available in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
More than 60 agricultural sightseeing spots have been built and
pulled in 100 million yuan (12 million US dollars) in business
last year, and 100 more are reported to be under construction.
</P>
<P>
People from Beijing's downtown area can refresh themselves on
the beautiful hillsides amidst the clear water, dining on good
food, fishing in ponds, or picking fruit in orchids, and if the
fancy strikes them, they can even join the villagers in their farm
chores.
</P>
<P>
This gives young people growing up in the city a good chance to
learn about agriculture, the manager of the Chaolai farm garden,
which had 30,000 visitors last year, explains. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
