<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 30 Kenyans Killed in Border Raid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- More than 30 Pokot herdsmen living
in western Kenya have been killed in an ambush by Karamojong
raiders from Uganda.
</P>
<P>
The attackers Thursday ambushed more than 200 Pokot youths who
were taking their animals for grazing at West Pokot's Lopitit
area, only five kilometers from the border, the Daily Nation
newspaper reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
There was a fierce exchange of fire Thursday morning before
the Karamojong escaped, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
In the wake of the killing, some residents fled their homes,
fearing further attacks. A group of 20 local businessmen also
closed their businesses.
</P>
<P>
The raid comes barely a month after the Kenyan government
deployed troops in western and central areas, including West
Pokot, to recover guns which were being used in tribal attacks
between the Pokots and Marakwets there.
</P>
<P>
There is a history of cross-border raids between the
Karamojong and Pokots, as well as the Karamojong and Turkanas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
