<HEADLINE> French Science Fiction Film Showing In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The film "Around The World In 80
Days", made jointly by Chinese and German film-makers using
puppets, had its premiere in the city of Shanghai today.
</P>
<P>
The film is based on the science fiction novel of the same
name, by the French writer Jules Verne.
</P>
<P>
It follows the global incidents of a man who is challenged in a
gambling incident, and reflects a theme of trusting on science,
acting in accordance with the law, and being ready to help others
as the means to leading a happy life.
</P>
<P>
The film was the second cooperative venture of the Shanghai
Animated Film Studio and the Manfred Durniok Film and Television
Production Company in shooting film based on world famous fiction.
</P>
<P>
They previously produced the fairy tales "Snow White and the
Frog Prince", using paper cuttings, in 1997. 
