<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Airport Regarded Significant for Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The grand opening here on
Thursday of the new Hong Kong International Airport by Chinese
President Jiang Zemin is of special significance as it will inject
new vitality into Hong Kong by boosting the people's confidence,
newspapers here said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The new airport, a multi-billion-dollar project completed after
eight years' construction, is located on a 1,248-hectare reclaimed
site at Chek Lap Kok off the northern coast of Lantau Island, 25
kilometers west of the Hong Kong Island. Operating around the
clock, the airport has a designed capacity of handling 35 million
passengers and three million tons of cargo a year.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang's appearance at the opening of the new airport
demonstrated the central government's firm support for Hong Kong's
major infrastructure projects and its efforts to promote economic
development, said an editorial of Chinese-language newspaper Wen
Wei Po.
</P>
<P>
"President Jiang also brought the good wishes of the people in
the motherland to the Hong Kong people who are making efforts to
further promote business and trade through worldwide cooperation,"
it said.
</P>
<P>
The new international airport, one of the most advanced
airports in the world today, will help guarantee that Hong Kong
remains the most prosperous international center for
transportation, trade, finance and tourism with broadest
international links, the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
On the historic day of July 2, 1998, President Jiang's special
plane was the first aircraft to take off from the airport after
its official opening while several hours later, U.S. President
Bill Clinton's special plane became the first aircraft to land at
the very same airport, the newspaper noted.
</P>
<P>
"The opening of the new airport amid the Southeast Asian
financial turmoil will encourage Hong Kong people to forge ahead
in this difficult time, help each other and aim high for more
achievements," it added.
</P>
<P>
"New Airport Injects Vitality Into Hong Kong for a New
Takeoff," reads the title of a Friday editorial of the local
newspaper Hong Kong Commercial Daily.
</P>
<P>
The opening of the new airport by President Jiang before his
departure from Hong Kong and the beginning of its commercial
operation will greatly increase Hong Kong's exchanges with the
mainland of the motherland and countries and regions in other
parts of the world, the editorial said.
</P>
<P>
"The new airport will inject new vitality into Hong Kong's
economic development and help consolidate Hong Kong's status as an
international and regional center of finance, trade, aviation and
tourism and enhance its competitiveness in the world.
</P>
<P>
"Working as one through concerted efforts, Hong Kong residents
can certainly overcome temporary difficulties and achieve a new
economic takeoff," the newspaper added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
