<HEADLINE> Major Computer Companies Start Scholarship Program In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Intel, Microsoft, Citizen, Green
Apple, and other major computer companies have decided to launch a
joint scholarship program in China to stimulate computer use among
China's young people.
</P>
<P>
The program was proposed by Hong Kong China Resources
(Holdings) Co. Ltd.'s Telecommunications (China) Electronics Co.,
and will start on July 5.
</P>
<P>
The amount of scholarship funds available is 1.2 million yuan,
and it will be used mainly for primary and middle school students
in Beijing and Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Anyone who buys a computer from designated shops in the two
cities between July 5 and September 30 can apply for the
scholarship, which will be awarded to 400 students, depending on
exam marks, by the end of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Computers are becoming more popular in China. In Shanghai, 8 to
10 percent of its 13 million people now have computers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
