<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rapid Growth For Private Sector In Northeastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The private sector of China's
Liaoning Province has grown dramatically in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning had more than 1.14 million private businesses by the
end of last year, employing more than 1.82 million people, with
32.1 billion yuan in output value and 13 million yuan in turnover.
</P>
<P>
The private sector grew by an average of 21 percent in the past
five years, double the growth of the province's GDP. The private
sector now accounts for 17.1 percent of the province's economy, up
from a mere 6 percent five years ago.
</P>
<P>
The private sector has developed more rapidly in the
countryside than in urban areas and displaced workers have
increasingly come to find jobs in private business.
</P>
<P>
Laid-off workers account for 44 percent of the people
employed by private business, but many work in the agricultural
and service sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
