<DOCNO> XIE19980703.0226 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> President Foresees Closer Kazakh-Sino Ties with Jiang's Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan is looking toward
trade and cooperation with China to boost its economic
development, says Kazakhstan President Nursultan Nazarbayev.
</P>
<P>
Relations between the two countries were particularly good
since the formulation of a border agreement, according to
Nazarbayev.
</P>
<P>
Now the two countries are preparing to sign another agreement,
casting a final settlement over the last two disputed border areas
when Chinese President Jiang Zemin visits Kazakhstan on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's last visit in 1996 set a new course in Sino-Kazakh
ties, establishing a friendship for the next century, said
Nazarbayev.
</P>
<P>
Just days before Jiang's attendance to the Alma Ata summit
between China, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Russia and Tajikistan and
his visit to Kazakhstan, Nazarbayev spoke to Chinese journalists
about Sino-Kazakh relations and the five-nation talks.
</P>
<P>
Economic cooperation with China was one way that leads
Kazakhstan into the world economic system, Nazarbayev said, adding
that both countries have stepped up cooperation in recent years
and border trade especially had been brisk, with a series of new
border ports opening up.
</P>
<P>
As one of Kazakhstan's main investors, China was ready to
participate in the construction of the new capital of Kazakhstan,
Nazarbayev said.
</P>
<P>
The two countries' economic cooperation however is still in its
early stages and thus had tremendous prospects for further
development, the president said.
</P>
<P>
China enjoyed prestige in the fields of politics, the military,
economy, culture and science and China played a important role
which could not be ignored in fighting the southeast Asian
economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
Nazarbayev reiterated his country's stand against separatism,
saying it opposed separatism in any form and supported China's
stand of non-division and territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan upheld this principle not only in the terms of
Sino-Kazakh relations but throughout the region and the world, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The leaders of the five nations signed a series of important
documents in 1996 in Shanghai and in 1997 in Moscow, thus
establishing the military confidence in the area bordering the
former Soviet Union and China and beginning the reduction of
troops stationed along the thousands of kilometers of border
areas, Nazarbayev said.
</P>
<P>
These documents have done much to build friendship and mutual
trust across the vast area of the Asian continent, Nazarbayev
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
