<BODY>
<HEADLINE> hke - Ukrainian Cabinet Passes Revised 1998 Draft Budget </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Ukrainian cabinet endorsed the
revised version of the draft 1998 national budget on Thursday,
cutting the deficit to 2.3 percent of the gross domestic product
(GDP).
</P>
<P>
Under the new draft, deficits for 1998 were reduced from 3.38
billion gryvnas (about 1.6 billion U.S. dollars) to 2.34 billion
gryvnas (about 1.1 billion U.S. dollars), according to an official
from the Ministry of Finance.
</P>
<P>
Cabinet sources disclosed that the new draft forecasts revenues
of 17.787 billion gryvnas (about 8.7 billion U.S. dollars), 3.3
billion gryvnas (about 1.6 billion U.S. dollars) less than the
former draft, and spending of 20.127 billion gryvnas (about 9.8
billion U.S. dollars), 4.4 billion gryvnas (about 2.1 billion
U.S. dollars) less.
</P>
<P>
The amount of foreign debt used to pay for the state debt and
deficit was also decreased from 3.079 billion U.S. dollars to
2.882 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Early this year, Ukraine's financial crisis intensified with
its deficits for the first quarter far exceeding the standard set
by the International Monetary Fund (IMF).
</P>
<P>
To fulfill the IMF's demand of a deficit of no more than 2.5
percent of the GDP, Ukraine's cabinet needed to revise its 1998
budget. The draft is due to be submitted to the parliament for
ratification. 
</P>
</TEXT>
