<HEADLINE> Chinese President Arrives in Kazakstan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
arrived here on Friday morning to attend the meeting of China,
Kazakstan, Kyrgyzstan, Russia and Tajikistan, and pay a working
visit to Kazakstan.
</P>
<P>
Kazak President Nursultan A. Nazarbayev presided over a
welcoming ceremony in honor of Jiang, who is on his first trip
abroad since he was re-elected Chinese president last March, at
the airport.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the welcoming ceremony were Kazak Minister of
Transport and Communications Erkin Kaliev, Kazak Ambassador to
China Kuanysh Sultanov.
</P>
<P>
The meeting of the five nations in Alma-Ata will focus on
regional security and economic cooperation, said sources from the
Chinese Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin, Kazak President Nazarbayev,
Kyrgyz President Askar A. Akayev, Tajik President Emomali
S. Rakhmono and Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov, who is
entrusted as the special representative of Russian President Boris
Yeltsin, will attend the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The five-nation meeting will issue a joint statement, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's entourage includes his wife Wang Yeping, Vice-Premier
Qian Qichen and Qian's wife Zhou Hanqiong, Zeng Qinghong, member
of the Secretariat of the Central Committee of the Communist Party
of China (CPC) and director of the General Office of the CPC
Central Committee, Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan and Zeng Peiyan,
minister in charge of the State Development Planning Commission.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Alma-Ata, Jiang will meet separately with
Kyrgyz President Akayev, Tajik President Rakhmonov, Russian
Foreign Minister Primakov.
</P>
<P>
Jiang is also scheduled to hold talks with his Kazak
counterpart Nazarbayev and the two presidents will attend the
signing ceremony of an additional agreement on border issues
between the two countries. 
