<HEADLINE> Thai Rice Exports Up Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's rice exports totaled
3.29 million tons worth 45.33 billion baht (1.1 billion U.S.
dollars) in the first half of this year, according to the Thai
Commerce Ministry.
</P>
<P>
In the same period of last year, Thailand exported 2.35 million
tons of rice.
</P>
<P>
Although exports to the Philippines and Indonesia had declined
because of those countries' economic problems, demand from other
markets was rising, especially from Africa, the Middle East and
Latin America, Commerce Minister Supachai Panitchpakdi was quoted
Friday by the newspaper The Bangkok Post as saying.
</P>
<P>
The low paddy output from key producers India and Pakistan
would boost Thai rice exports in the third quarter, Supachai said.
</P>
<P>
Between 400,000 and 500,000 tons of rice would be exported in
the period, with shipments for the year likely to top the target
of 5.3 million tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
