<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Build Old Town into Tourist Site </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Longhua Town in Shanghai has
launched a large-scale project to turn itself into a tourist spot
by building a number of recreational, shopping and catering places
around the Longhua Temple and Longhua Pagoda.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to be completed by 2005, according to
the official plan stipulated by the municipal government and the
district government of Xuhui, where the old town is located.
</P>
<P>
Longhua Town, with its 1,750-year-old temple and pagoda, as
well as other tourist attractions, used to be a holiday site for
local residents in Shanghai, the largest metropolis in China.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the National Tourism Administration made the Longhua
Tourist Zone a major tourist project in Shanghai.  
