<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Builds New Water Theme Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 3 (Xinhua) -- A new theme park fed with water
from the Funan River, reportedly the first of its kind in the
world, has opened in Chengdu, capital of of southwest China's
Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
The park features a river water environment, purification
facilities and educational exhibits.
</P>
<P>
The complex, which is in the shape of a fish and covers 24,000
sq.m., was jointly designed by an American environmentalist and
specialists from China, the United States and the Republic of
Korea.
</P>
<P>
The goal is to enhance the awareness in protecting water
environments. The facility, which highlights the theme that water,
the environment and life rely heavily on one another, shows the
natural water purification process in the Funan River.
</P>
<P>
The river water is diverted into the park and flows through
sculptures, a plant pond and a fish pond. The water is purified
throughout the process and flows back to the river.
</P>
<P>
The city has allocated some 2.7 billion yuan over the past five
years to harnessing the river, with the effort reported to be the
largest environmental protection project in China's urban areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980703.0249 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
