<HEADLINE> Heilongjiang Reports Rapid Border Trade Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Border trade between northeast
China's Heilongjiang Province and Russia has continued to increase
steadily, official figures indicate.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang's border trade volume totaled 300 million U.S.
dollars in the first five months of this year, a surge of 33
percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang's border trade with Russia hit bottom in 1994 and
1995 before the downward trend was reversed in 1996, when the
volume reached 750 million U.S. dollars, an increase of 28.9
percent over the previous year. Last year the Chinese province's
border trade with Russia rocketed 42.5 percent to 1 billion
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that Heilongjiang's exports have been
well-received in Russia as product quality improves.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang has also formulated a number of policies since
1996 to guide the healthy growth of border trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
