<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Navy Destroy Rebel Boats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan Navy Wednesday night
destroyed a flotilla of Sea Tiger of the Tamil rebels off the
country's eastern coast, according to reports reaching here
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The reports said the navy had detected and engaged about 16
rebel craft off Kuchchuvelu in Eastern Province. Several of the
vessels were sunk and 48 rebel cadres are said to have been killed
in the four-hour confrontation.
</P>
<P>
Two sailors were slightly wounded in the incident. There were
several large ships in the flotilla and it is believed that the
rebel convoy was transporting arms and ammunition and more cadres
to reinforce units facing government troops, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
In another incident at Pungututhivu off the Jaffna peninsula,
25 rebel cadres are reported killed while the navy lost two
personnel with four wounded on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a war against the
government for separate stated in the north and east of the
country since 1983. 
</P>
