<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavian President Slobodan
Milosevic Thursday urged the ethnic Albanian leaders in Kosovo to
resume talks with the federal authorities to achieve progress in
solving the Kosovo conflict.
</P>
<P>
Milosevic's call came after a briefing by Foreign Minister
Zivorad Jovanovic and Chairman of the Foreign and Political
Affairs Committee of the federal parliament Ljubisa Ristic, Tanjug
news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The resumption of talks, the only way toward the solution of
the Kosovo issue, was in the interests of the province's ethnic
Albanians, the president reiterated.
</P>
<P>
The federal government's stand on Kosovo remained unchanged,
Milosevic said. To ensure equality among all citizens and between
all nationalities, the government would continue to push a
political and peaceful solution.
</P>
<P>
Based upon the United Nations Charter, OSCE (the Organization
for Security and Cooperation in Europe) standard and the Helsinki
principles, the Yugoslavian government would make Kosovo an
autonomous area within Serbia. However Milosevic said that
autonomy should not be at the cost of the territorial integrity
and sovereignty of Serbia and the Yugoslav Federation. 
