<HEADLINE> Chile's Unemployment Rate Declines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Chile's unemplyment rate reach 5.6
percent in the period between March and May, a decline of 0.7
percent from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
A report released lately by the National Statistics Institute
indicated that the total workforce for the March-May period stood
at 5,691,090 people, an percent of two percent over the same
period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the total number of people with a job stood at
5,370,330 people, an increase of 2.8 percent over the March-May
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, the unemployment rate by gender was 5
percent for men and 7 percent for women, with a decline of 0.4
percent and 1.3 percent respectively from the same period of last
year. 
