<HEADLINE> China's Inner Mongolia Reports Steady Export Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, July 3 (Xinhua) -- North China's Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region has reported steady export growth this year.
</P>
<P>
The region's exports totaled 380 million U.S. dollars in the
first six months of this year, up 16.5 percent from the
corresponding period of last year. The growth rate is about 7
percent higher than the national figure during the period.
</P>
<P>
To counter the effects of the Asian financial crisis, Inner
Mongolia this year has taken various measures to improve its
export mix and develop its processing and tourism trade.
</P>
<P>
As exports to the Republic of Korea and countries in Southeast
Asian slumped, Inner Mongolia stepped up efforts to increase
exports to Russia and Mongolia. The region's exports to the two
countries surged 44 percent to more than 88 million U.S. dollars
between January and May.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Inner Mongolia has increased efforts to contract
more overseas projects and thereby boost exports of local products.
</P>
<P>
The region reported 56 million U.S. dollars in contracted
foreign direct investment in the first five months, 2.2 times the
figure for the same period last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
