<HEADLINE> Peruvian Woman Bears Baby of Unusual Weight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, July 2 (Xinhua) -- A Peruvian woman gave birth to a 6.5
kilogram baby in the city of Arequipa, 1,000 kilometers south of
Lima, the local press reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The "superbaby" was born in the Goyeneche Hospital of Arequipa,
where he was put under intensive care inside an incubator, because
he presents apnea symptoms, hospital authorities were quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The unusual delivery occurred two days ago, when the medics
decided to perform a Caesarean operation on Mrs. Epifania Anco de
Huachani, 40, because the difficulties presented for a normal
delivery.
</P>
<P>
The medics attributed the weight of the baby to a genetic
defect caused by the diabetes that has affected the mother for
many years.
</P>
<P>
Cesar Solorzano, the medic in charge of the delivery, hinted
that the infant might be suffering some kind of ailment, since his
heart does not work as it should.
</P>
<P>
Epifania, mother of other four children, said neither she nor
her husband have a steady job. "I do not know what will be the
fate of my family, since we have economic problems and my new baby
might have some illness that will cause more spending," she
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
