<HEADLINE> World Bank Backs Reconstruction Efforts in Azerbaijan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved here
Thursday an interest-free credit of 20 million U.S. dollar
equivalent to support reconstruction efforts in Azerbaijan.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be used to assist in the repatriation of
internally displaced people as a result of the Nagomo-Karabakh
conflict, and to raise their standard of living.
</P>
<P>
The project consists six components of relocation and the
voluntary resettlement, reconstruction and repair of housing,
creation of employment, health and education as well as
infrastructure and energy construction.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is some 54.2 million dollars,
including contingencies.
</P>
<P>
Since Azerbaijan joined the World Bank in 1992 and the
International Development Association, the World Bank's
concessional lending affiliate in 1995, the country has received
some 310 million dollars financing for nine projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
