<HEADLINE> Denmark Supports Romania's Admission to NATO, EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Romania's admission to European
and Euro-Atlantic bodies will be both to the interest of Romania
and the interest of Denmark, Danish Foreign Minister Niels Helveg
Petersen told the press in Bucharest Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Niels Helveg Petersen, who is on a one-day official visit in
Romania, said that the main reason for his current visit to
Romania was to find first-hand facts about Romania's demarches for
intergration into the European Union (EU) since Denmark was deeply
engaged in the process of EU enlargement.
</P>
<P>
The Danish government was pleading for the EU's extension since
this was the main element that can guarantee Europe's long-term
stability and security, the minister added.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated Denmark's support for Romania's admission to both
structures, saying Denmark wanted to be part of a strong and
enlarged EU.
</P>
<P>
Petersen also voiced his "conviction that an increase in the
support funds would be necessary in a pre-admission phase, a
difficult phase, when the applying countries need more substantial
backing."
</P>
<P>
In his visit, the Danish minister had talks with his Romanian
counterpart Andrei Plesu and was received by Prime Minister Radu
Vasile. He also met with Speaker of the Chamber of Deputies Ion
Diaconescu and Senate President Petre Roman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
