<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Return Anniversary Marked in Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FRANKFURT, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Trade Development
Council and the Hong Kong Economic and Trade Office held a
cocktail reception here Thursday to mark the first anniversary of
Hong Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the reception which was attended by over 400
prominent figures from German political and business circles, Lore
Buscher, director of the Hong Kong Trade Development Council
Office in Frankfurt, outlined the bright future for Hong Kong
despite the negative impact from the recent Asian financial
crisis.
</P>
<P>
The past 12 months had demonstrated the smooth and successful
implementation of the "one country, two systems" principle which
gives Hong Kong a high degree of autonomy, she said.
</P>
<P>
The lifestyle of Hong Kong people remained intact and business
went on as usual in Hong Kong, she added.
</P>
<P>
On the recent Asian financial crisis, Buscher said, "Despite
the negative impact of the crisis, Hong Kong is clearly in a
better shape when compared with its neighbors."
</P>
<P>
She also expressed the belief that Hong Kong economy would
recover as the first from the crisis thanks to a number of unique
factors, including its transparent finance system with
well-functioned supervision mechanism, the stable currency, the
budget surplus and sufficient foreign exchange reserves as well as
its close links with the Chinese hinterland.
</P>
<P>
"With Hong Kong people's imaginativeness, flexibility, their
ability to adapt quickly to changed situations, along with a wise
economic policy and the traditionally high degree of stability and
economic freedom, the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region will
be able to master the current difficult situation," Buscher said.
</P>
<P>
At the reception, a photo exhibition was also put on show on
Hong Kong's new airport, which is due to start operation on July 6
to give a great boost to Hong Kong's role as a regional
transportation and aviation center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
