<HEADLINE> Greece, Zimbabwe Sign Military Cooperation Accords </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Greece and Zimbabwe signed here
Thursday agreements to strengthen military cooperation between the
two countries, including cooperation in the defense industries.
</P>
<P>
Under the accords signed by Greek Defense Minister Akis
Tsohatzopoulos and his visiting Zimbabwean counterpart Moven
Mahachi, Greece will also assist Zimbabwe in training senior
military officers, pilots and doctors, and removing landmines in
the African country.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after their talks, Tsohatzopoulos said that Zimbabwe
backed the United Nations' efforts for a single, democratic and
just solution for the Cyprus problem.
</P>
<P>
While supporting the ethnic Albanians's efforts for broad
autonomy and self-administration in the Yugoslav province of
Kosovo, the minister said that it was "unacceptable" for
minorities using force in the name of self-determination to try
and change the present borders in the Balkan region.
</P>
<P>
He opposed a military intervention to the Kosovo problem,
warning that this would be a catastrophe which would affect the
surrounding region. 
</P>
