<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Finances Colombia Toll Road Concession Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Thursday approved
a 137.1 million U.S. dollar loan for Colombia for the toll road
concession project.
</P>
<P>
The project will improve transport conditions along a strategic
road corridor linking Bogota with Medelin, the two most populous
and industrialized cities of the country, and the ports on the
north coast through an effective and sustainable private-public
partnership.
</P>
<P>
The project supports the government's strategy to increase
private sector participation in modernizing its road network. The
strategy is expected to improve efficiency, mobilize additional
resources to provide more rapidly the services for which users are
willing to pay, and reduce the fiscal impact of the modernization
program. The private sector will provide about 70 percent of the
financing.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is some 572.3 million dollars. In
addition to the World Bank loan, private project sponsors will
provide 395.1 million dollars. Revenues generated from the
operation of roads under the project will finance the remaining
40.1 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
